      <div class="main">
        <section>
          Our wedding will take place in Boston on Saturday, October 21, 2017 at <a href="http://www.stceciliaboston.org">St. Cecilia's Parish</a> at 1pm, with a cocktail reception to follow immediately at <a href="http://www.mayhewwine.com">Mayhew Wine Shop</a>. Transportation will be provided to our reception following the ceremony.
          <p>Please arrive for our ceremony no later than 12:45pm.</p>
          St. Cecilia's is located in Boston's bustling Back Bay neighborhood, and Mayhew Wine Shop recently opened in the red-hot Fort Point district. Both venues are within walking distance of numerous public transit options, and journeys by taxi and ride-share apps are always seconds away.
          <p>Both of our venues are handicap-accessible, but our transportation is not. Please inform Meghan or Johnny if you are in need of accessible transportation!</p>

          <h3><em>Parking:</em></h3> If you plan on driving to our ceremony, the closest garages to St. Cecilia's are <a href="http://www.patparking.com/haviland.html">Haviland St. Garage</a> ($15) and <a href="http://pilgrimparking.com/boston-parking-garages/hynes-auditorium-garage.htm">Hynes Auditorium Garage</a> ($20-25). This being said, you might consider parking at <a href="http://www.neccogarage.com/">Necco Street Garage</a>, which is a 2 minute walk from our reception and only $5 for the day. A taxi/Lyft/Uber from there to our ceremony averages $10-16, and you won't need to worry about transportation back! There is street parking throughout Boston, but it can be notoriously difficult to find a spot.
          <br />
          If at all possible, we strongly suggest availing yourself of <a href="http://mbta.com">public transportation</a>. Services such as Lyft and Uber are also on-demand 24/7, and taxis are plentiful.
